<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MTA39">
<l>iṭantatu pūmi yeṭuttatu kuṉṟaṅ</l>
<l>kaṭantatu kañcaṉaimuṉ ṉañcak – kiṭantatuvu</l>
<l>nīrōta mākaṭalē niṉṟatuvum vēṅkaṭamē</l>
<l>pērōta vaṇṇar peritu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Digging up the earth, lifting the mountain,</l>
<l>prevailing over Kaṃsa<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Further references to Kṛṣṇa’s uncle and arch enemy Kaṃsa are found in Pū. 89.1, 92.1, Pē. 34.4.</note>, once to be feared,</l>
<l>lying on the great ocean with water floods and standing on Vēṅkaṭam</l>
<l>is what is great in the one the colour of the great flood.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
